cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.IR

This paper deals with web privacy and the disclosure of third-party data collection in website privacy policies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves analyzing data flows on websites, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The study also examines the readability and understandability of privacy policies, which could be categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper involves auditing policies to determine if they respect the "Do Not Track" signal, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
